org.pragmaticminds.crunch.api.windowed.extractor

Interface GroupAggregationFinalizer<T extends Serializable>

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Serializable
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    DefaultGenericEventGroupAggregationFinalizer
    Functional Interface:
    This is a functional interface and can therefore be used as the assignment target for a lambda expression or method reference.

    @FunctionalInterface
public interface GroupAggregationFinalizer<T extends Serializable>
extends Serializable
    This represents the last step of processing in a GroupByExtractor. This class gets a map of named resulting values. With this Map this class creates resulting GenericEvents which than go out for processing of the next steps.
    Author:
    Erwin Wagasow Created by Erwin Wagasow on 16.08.2018

        void onFinalize(Map<String,Object> aggregatedValues,
                EvaluationContext<T> context)
        Packs the aggregated values into resulting GenericEvents.
        Parameters:
        aggregatedValues - is a map of all aggregated values, that can be further processed and be added as parameters into the resulting GenericEvents.
        context - current from the evaluation call. Takes the resulting GenericEvents, with the aggregated values as parameters.
